rComments: Really great prof, and she has extremely detailed and helpful slides (part are available online, but she fills in the details if you attend). Midterm wasn't too bad (average was 75%), but the criteria was extremely clear and if you follow the lectures, it isn't too bad at all. Interesting class that I took to fill a spot, but I ended up loving it

I have her at the U of A shes new this year but Im glad she came here because shes such a great professor. I didnt know what to expect cause Im not in social science but this is my favorite class so far. Her lectures are interesting and she brings in really good examples and people pay attention. Would recommend this class
best prof I have had by far!

Shes fun and smart and pretty tough but fair. The TA didn't have office hours but the prof stayed after class every week until the last person was done asking questions. The avg was 67% by the way (last poster wrong). Shes really young too so u can tell shes only gonna improve and be a great prof. Wud take another class w her

As a person, she is humble & respectful. As a professor, however, she is not too bad but there are few things that needs to be improved. For instance, there were no office hrs for the TA & prof. Tests were also quite challenging. Also, she didn't bell-curve the midterm (worth 35%) even though majority of the class did poorly (class avg was 60%)
She was actually my TA for this course. I would say she's tough but fair. You have to really listen to what she wants on papers and exams.
